Misleading dealership tactics. I was interested in a used trailer that RideNow had on their website. The price listed on the website was $599. I called to make sure it was still there, then drove nearly an hour to check it out. I looked at the trailer and was told to sit and wait for the sales manager. About 30 minutes later, the sales manager finally comes out with a quote sheet for over $1,300. $129 in service fees (why wasn't that reflected in the list price?), $400 in doc fees (ridiculous) and $125 registration fee (no problem) plus tax (of course). If you are considering dealing with them, you might want to get a written quote before making the drive.

